```

## Design System & Branding

### DevFest Brand Guidelines
This project follows official Google DevFest branding guidelines:

**Primary Colors:**
- Blue: `#4285F4` (Google Blue) - Primary CTAs, headings
- Red: `#EA4335` (Google Red) - Accents, important elements
- Yellow: `#FBBC04` (Google Yellow) - Highlights, warnings
- Green: `#34A853` (Google Green) - Success states, environmental themes

**Typography:**
- Primary: Roboto (Google Sans fallback)
- Monospace: Roboto Mono (for code/technical content)
- Font loading: `display: 'swap'` for performance

**Custom CSS Classes (globals.css):**
- `.devfest-card` - Standard card styling
- `.devfest-heading-1/2/3` - Consistent heading hierarchy
- `.devfest-body` - Body text styling
- `.devfest-surface` - Surface/background colors
- `.devfest-lines` - Border colors

### Design Patterns
- **Mobile-first responsive design** - All components built for mobile, then desktop
- **Smooth scroll navigation** - `scroll-smooth` on html element
- **Google's Material Design** principles - Cards, elevation, shadows
- **High contrast** - WCAG AA compliance for accessibility

## Development Conventions

### Component Structure
Each major section is a separate component in `/src/components/`:
- `Navigation.tsx` - Fixed header with logo and nav links
- `Hero.tsx` - (Legacy - not currently used)
- `ReadyToJoin.tsx` - Hero section with registration CTA
- `WhatToExpect.tsx` - Event highlights grid
- `WhyAttend.tsx` - Target audience sections
- `EventVenue.tsx` - Venue information with images
- `SpeakersNew.tsx` - Speaker showcase
- `GetInvolvedNew.tsx` - Volunteer/sponsor/speak opportunities
- `BuildFutureAI.tsx` - AI-focused content section
- `SponsorsPartnersNew.tsx` - Sponsor and partner logos
- `OurMission.tsx` - Mission statement and values
- `Footer.tsx` - Contact info, social links

**Naming Convention:**
- New/updated components have "New" suffix (e.g., `SpeakersNew.tsx`)
- Legacy components kept for reference but not imported
- Use descriptive, section-based names

### Code Style
```typescript
// ✅ Good Practices
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props
- Export default function for components
- Use 'use client' directive when needed (interactivity, hooks)
- Semantic HTML (main, section, article, nav, footer)
- Descriptive alt text for all images
- External links: target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"

// ❌ Avoid
- Inline styles (use Tailwind classes)
- Magic numbers (use Tailwind spacing scale)
- console.log in production (removed via next.config.ts)
- Large components (split into smaller, focused components)
```

### Image Handling
```typescript
// Use Next.js Image component with optimization
import Image from 'next/image'

<Image
  src="/path/to/image.jpg"
  alt="Descriptive alt text"
  width={1200}
  height={600}
  className="w-full h-auto"
  priority={false}  // true only for above-fold images
/>

// Formats: WebP and AVIF enabled in next.config.ts
// Device sizes: Configured for responsive breakpoints
```

