## Development Workflow

### Getting Started
```bash
npm install           # Install dependencies
npm run dev          # Start dev server with Turbopack (http://localhost:3000)
npm run build        # Production build
npm run lint         # Run ESLint
```

### Git Workflow
- **Main branch:** Production-ready code (auto-deploys to Vercel)
- **Feature branches:** Use descriptive names (e.g., `feature/speaker-profiles`)
- **No force pushes to main** - Protect the main branch
- **Commit messages:** Clear, descriptive (e.g., "Add speaker profile section")

### Testing Checklist
Before pushing changes:
- [ ] Test on mobile viewport (375px width minimum)
- [ ] Test on desktop (1920px+ width)
- [ ] Verify all links work
- [ ] Check image loading and alt text
- [ ] Run `npm run build` to verify production build
- [ ] Test navigation menu (desktop and mobile)
- [ ] Verify no console errors

## AI Assistant Guidelines

### When Making Changes
1. **Preserve DevFest branding** - Don't change colors, fonts, or design tokens
2. **Maintain accessibility** - WCAG AA compliance minimum
3. **Keep mobile-first** - Always test mobile viewport first
4. **Use existing patterns** - Follow component structure of current code
5. **Optimize images** - Always use Next.js Image component with proper sizing
6. **SEO matters** - Include meta tags, alt text, semantic HTML
7. **Performance first** - Lazy load, optimize bundles, minimize client-side JS

### Making Component Updates
```typescript
// Template for new section components
'use client'  // Only if needed for interactivity

import Image from 'next/image'
import Link from 'next/link'
// Import other dependencies

export default function ComponentName() {
  return (
    <section id="section-name" className="py-16 px-6 bg-devfest-surface">
      <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
        <h2 className="devfest-heading-1 text-center mb-8">
          Section Title
        </h2>
        {/* Content */}
      </div>
    </section>
  )
}
```

### Adding New Pages
1. Create folder in `/src/app/[page-name]/`
2. Add `page.tsx` with component
3. Export metadata object with title, description, keywords
4. Update Navigation component with new link
5. Test routing and navigation

### Common Tasks
- **Add sponsor logo:** Place in `/public/sponsors/`, update array in SponsorsPartnersNew.tsx
- **Add speaker:** Update speaker array in SpeakersNew.tsx component
- **Update event details:** Check layout.tsx metadata, Footer.tsx, EventVenue.tsx
- **Change colors:** Modify globals.css design tokens (but preserve DevFest brand)
- **Add new section:** Create component, import in page.tsx, add to navigation

